                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#86v #87r"/> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#94r #94v"/> (tenth Biblical Canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d01">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#1r #6r #16v #29r #33r #47v #53v #58r #78r #87v #97v #103v"/> (haräg);
                  <locus target="#5v #11r #23v #39v #53r #57v #67r #75v #77v #87r #97r #103r"/> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#47r"/> (line of black ink);
                  <locus target="#82v"/> (line of black dots)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a01">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>": pentrial and note of secondary ownership, in a crude hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a02">
                    <desc type="PurchaseNote">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)"/>": Record of transaction of the book: “Näḥase  2, 1929 (EC). I, Mämǝre Wäldä Maryam, sold one Ethiopian Dawit with it’s maḥdär to Mämǝre Ṣǝge for two birr. I swear by the soul of the King and if anyone makes a claim I will refund the cost.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a03">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iir(ecto)"/>": A note about something that happened in 1871 EC (= 1878–9), perhaps the establishmen of the Church of Saint Mary.  A seal is included
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a04">
                    <desc type="Record">
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)"/>": Record of the birth of a person: “Ṭərr 2, 1879 EC, in the year of Luke the Evangelist, Mämǝre Ṣǝge was born.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e01">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#43v"/>: the mid-point of the Psalms is marked with the second letter of each word being written in red ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e02">
                    <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 19
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e03">
                    <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    red yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#23"/>;
                    white string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#39"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e04">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–10
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e05">
                    <desc>
                    A few of the sections in Psalm 118 contain the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e06">
                    <desc>
                    Scribal intervention:
                    words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#7r #9r #13r #16r #21v"/>, etc.);
                    and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1v #6r #20v #28r #63v"/>, etc.);
                    text has been removed (<locus target="#9r #13r #17r #39v #45v"/>, etc.)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
